# Check influence of gap between contacting bins to the hybridisation trend 
################################################################################
1. Per chr, split contacts into having short (gap <= splitLength) or long gap 
(gap > splitLength) between contacting bins. splitLength is supplied in terms of
bin. Contacts with NA hybridisation score (N's in bins) are excluded. After 
classifying contacts, there hybridisation scores are pulled from HYB.MX and
plotted. Note that in plot, all percentages are iin reference to the total number
of contacts in chr (including those with NA hyb scores). 
